What it is
\i0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs55\fsmilli27648 \cf2 \cb3 Upon hearing the term \'93Pavlovian,\'94 almost everyone thinks of the famous experiment by Ivan Pavlov in which a dog was conditioned to expect food when a bell was rung. Eventually, the dog started salivating as soon as the bell rang, even if no food was present.\cb1 \
\cb3 From birth, all animals and humans are equipped with a limited set of reflexes (i.e., genetically hard-wired responses to specific environmental stimuli). A reflex is the relationship between a specific environmental event or stimulus and a fixed behavioral action or response evoked by that stimulus. Because these reflexes are often critical to survival, they can affect our decision making fundamentally, often without our awareness.\cb1 \
